      "id": "t62",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "How much does a YouTuber with 1 million subscribers make?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t63",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Subscriber count doesn't directly determine income — views do. A 1M subscriber channel averaging 300K views/month at $5 RPM earns ~$1,500/month from AdSense. Sponsorships typically add 3–5× more."
    },
    {
      "id": "t64",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Do YouTubers get paid for old videos?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t65",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Yes — YouTube videos earn revenue indefinitely as long as they receive views and remain monetized. Older videos with strong search ranking can generate passive income for years."
    },
    {
      "id": "t66",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "What percentage of YouTube revenue do creators keep?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t67",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Creators keep approximately 55% of the AdSense revenue generated by their videos. YouTube retains the remaining 45%."
